Matsushita Electric Industrial Co Ltd&lt;MC.T>, Mazda Motor Corp &lt;MAZT.T> and Ford Motor Co &lt;F> havesigned an agreement to set up a joint venture to make car airconditioners in Japan, Matsushita said in a statement.    The new venture, &lt;Japan Climate Systems Corp> will becapitalised at 1.5 billion yen, and the three partners willhold equal shares.    The partners will invest 3.6 billion yen in constructing aplant in Hiroshima, due for completion in late 1988. The plantwill initially make 100,000 air conditioners a year for Mazda,it said. REUTER&#3;